parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear brake can cause a loss of control, accidents, or injuries, especially on loose or slippery surfaces, as the vehicle may not be able to slow down or stop in a timely manner.
symptoms: The rear brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the rear brake pedal goes to the bottom of its travel with little to no braking action
the rear brake requires multiple applications to build up pressure
the rear brake becomes temporarily functional after bleeding but fails again after a short distance or time.
